            <p> Regions that import more oil than they produce — including the United States, Europe, China, and India — can see trillions in gains to their economies over the next 20 years from reducing their oil consumption in favor of low-carbon alternatives. They can benefit by transitioning to a low-carbon economy together even if net oil producing countries do not.</p>
