            <h2>Coal fired power generation has slowed in the developed world</h2>
            <p>To be consistent with a 450ppm limit, these develop countries need to halt their development beyond the threshold.  In these mature economies, it woun’t be a big cost to stop. To meet the global goal, they can simply allow existing plants to retire naturally, and stop building new ones.</p>
