            <h2>Coal-fired power plants are critical energy assets today, but by retiring plants on schedule, and halting new development, future losses will be minimal.</h2>
            <p>Developed countries can reduce their coal-fired plants with minimal costs, simply by letting their 40 and 60 year old plants retire naturally  rather than refurbishing them.</p>
