            <p>To be consistent with a 450ppm limit, these developing countries need to halt their development beyond the threshold.  These growing economies have a tremendous opportunity to get energy development right the first time and then reap the benefits for decades to come. Continuing on a path of Coal will result in wasteful invesment, as new coal plants will simply be competing for emissions quotas with existing plants. Current investment will be future stranded asset costs that need to be written off as plants are shut down.  Those investment dollars could be used much more efficiently in alternative renewables.</p>
